<item>
            <title>[IO-187] FileSystemUtils.freeSpaceKb doesn&apos;t work with relative paths on Linux</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/IO-187</link>
                <project id="12310477" key="IO">Commons IO</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Calling FileSystemUtils.freeSpaceKb with &quot;.&quot;, &quot;./&quot;, &quot;../&quot;, &quot;../foo&quot; etc. will result in an empty string being passed to df.&lt;br/&gt;
freeSpaceKb calls FileNameUtils.normalize on the path which destroys relative paths.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I don&apos;t see any need to normalize the path so the fix is simply to remove that call.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>&lt;p&gt;Linux&lt;/p&gt;</environment>
